  43,57,"When the son of Mary was cited as an example ňĻin argumentňļ, your people ňĻO Prophetňļ broke into ňĻjoyfulňļ applause"
  43,58,"They exclaimed, ‚ÄúWhich is better: our gods or Jesus?‚ÄĚ They cite him only to argue. In fact, they are a people prone to dispute"
  43,59,"He was only a servant We showed favour to, and made as an example for the Children of Israel"
  43,60,"Had We willed, We could have easily replaced you ňĻallňļ with angels,¬†succeeding one another on earth"
  43,61,"And his ňĻsecondňļ coming is truly a sign for the Hour. So have no doubt about it, and follow me. This is the Straight Path"
  43,62,"And do not let Satan hinder you, ňĻforňļ he is certainly your sworn enemy"
  43,63,"When Jesus came with clear proofs, he declared, ‚ÄúI have come to you with wisdom, and to clarify to you some of what you differ about. So fear Allah, and obey me"
  43,64,"Surely Allah ňĻaloneňļ is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him ňĻaloneňļ. This is the Straight Path.‚ÄĚ"
  43,65,"Yet their ňĻvariousňļ groups have differed among themselves ňĻabout himňļ, so woe to the wrongdoers when they face the torment of a painful Day"
  43,66,Are they waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise when they least expect ňĻitňļ
  43,67,"Close friends will be enemies to one another on that Day, except the righteous"
  43,68,"ňĻwho will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúO My servants! There is no fear for you Today, nor will you grieve‚ÄĒ"
  43,69,ňĻthoseňļ who believed in Our signs and ňĻfullyňļ submitted ňĻto Usňļ
  43,70,"Enter Paradise, you and your spouses, rejoicing.‚ÄĚ"
  43,71,Golden trays and cups will be passed around to them. There will be whatever the souls desire and the eyes delight in. And you will be there forever
  43,72,That is the Paradise which you will be awarded for what you used to do
  43,73,There you will have abundant fruit¬†to eat from
  43,74,"Indeed, the wicked will be in the torment of Hell forever"
  43,75,"It will never be lightened for them, and there they will be overwhelmed with despair"
  43,76,"We did not wrong them, but it was they who were the wrongdoers"
  43,77,"They will cry, ‚ÄúO M√Ęlik!¬†Let your Lord finish us off.‚ÄĚ He will answer, ‚ÄúYou are definitely here to stay.‚ÄĚ"
  43,78,"We certainly brought the truth to you, but most of you were resentful of the truth"
  43,79,Or have they mastered some ňĻevilňļ plan? Then We ňĻtooňļ are surely planning
  43,80,"Or do they think that We do not hear their ňĻevilňļ thoughts and secret talks? Yes ňĻWe doňļ! And Our messenger-angels are in their presence, recording ňĻit allňļ"
  43,81,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf the Most Compassionate ňĻreallyňļ had offspring, I would be the first worshipper.‚ÄĚ"
  43,82,"Glorified is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, far above what they claim"
  43,83,"So let them indulge ňĻin falsehoodňļ and amuse ňĻthemselvesňļ until they face their Day, which they have been warned of"
  43,84,"It is He Who is ňĻthe onlyňļ God in the heavens and ňĻthe onlyňļ God on the earth. For He is the All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  43,85,And Blessed is the One to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between! With Him ňĻaloneňļ is the knowledge of the Hour. And to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned
  43,86,"ňĻButňļ those ňĻobjects of worshipňļ they invoke besides Him have no power to intercede, except those who testify to the truth knowingly"
  43,87,"If you ask them ňĻO Prophetňļ who created them, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúAllah!‚ÄĚ How can they then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  43,88,"ňĻAllah is Aware ofňļ the Prophet‚Äôs cry: ‚ÄúO my Lord! Indeed, these are a people who persist in disbelief.‚ÄĚ"
  43,89,So bear with them and respond with peace. They will soon come to know
