  44,6,"as a mercy from your Lord. He ňĻaloneňļ is truly the All-Hearing, All-Knowing‚ÄĒ"
  44,7,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, if only you had sure faith"
  44,8,"There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. He ňĻaloneňļ gives life and causes death. ňĻHe isňļ your Lord, and the Lord of your forefathers"
  44,9,"In fact, they are in doubt, amusing themselves"
  44,10,"Wait then ňĻO Prophetňļ for the day ňĻwhenňļ the sky will be veiled in haze,¬†clearly visible"
